emove and teardown events get called when .die() is used. Additionally made sure that default actions are triggered when namespaced events are used. Fixes #6202 and #6250.</p>\n</div>\";i:2;s:291:\"<div class=\"photo item\">\n<p><p>I&#8217;ve never felt so proud of our family name than to discover that such a TV was ever conceived. Absolute win with Hardcastle plastered all over it.</p></p>\n<img src=\"http://27.media.tumblr.com/tumblr_kz15zqGEkr1qzpuawo1_75sq.jpg\" alt=\"Templated\"/>\n</div>\";i:3;s:206:\"<div class=\"git item\">\n	<div class=\"commitTime\">14:03</div>\n	<p><strong>jQuery</strong>Removing the mention of buliding the docs from the README. Thanks to \'phihag\' in the forum for the heads-up.</p>\n</div>\";i:4;s:277:\"<div class=\"git item\">\n	<div class=\"commitTime\">14:03</div>\n	<p><strong>jQuery</strong>Landing a faster trim method. Based upon the work by Travis Hardiman and DBJDBJ. More details here: http://forum.jquery.com/topic/faster-jquery-trim Fixes #2279, #4452, and #4835.</p>\n</div>\";}'),(32,'5th March','a:3:{i:0;s:279:\"<div class=\"git fullItem\">\n	<div class=\"commitTime\">This is everyting14:03</div>\n	<p><strong>jQuery</strong>No need to use .call() anymore since we switched from .apply() for appendTo, etc. Thanks to Robert in 2c08004f6d4e7f11a875190e132d204a25cb9418 for the heads-up.</p>\n</div>\";i:1;s:276:\"<div class=\"git fullItem\">\n	<div class=\"commitTime\">This is everyting05:03</div>\n	<p><strong>jQuery</strong>I take that back! It was a bug, but the cache had to be triggered and a collection of cached nodes had to be passed in (an odd case to be sure). Fixes #6227.</p>\n</div>\";i:2;s:311:\"<div class=\"git fullItem\">\n	<div class=\"commitTime\">This is everyting05:03</div>\n	<p><strong>jQuery</strong>Attempted to fix #6227, not entirely sure if it\'s a problem as I\'m having a hard time reproducing it. Regardless, the change is harmless and potentially even speeds up appendTo, etc. slightly.</p>\n</div>\";}','a:3:{i:0;s:258:\"<div class=\"git item\">\n	<div class=\"commitTime\">14:03</div>\n	<p><strong>jQuery</strong>No need to use .call() anymore since we switched from .apply() for appendTo, etc. Thanks to Robert in 2c08004f6d4e7f11a875190e132d204a25cb9418 for the heads-up.</p>\n</div>\";i:1;s:255:\"<div class=\"git item\">\n	<div class=\"commitTime\">05:03</div>\n	<p><strong>jQuery</strong>I take that back! It was a bug, but the cache had to be triggered and a collection of cached nodes had to be passed in (an odd case to be sure). Fixes #6227.</p>\n</div>\";i:2;s:290:\"<div class=\"git item\">\n	<div class=\"commitTime\">05:03</div>\n	<p><strong>jQuery</strong>Attempted to fix #6227, not entirely sure if it\'s a problem as I\'m having a hard time reproducing it. Regardless, the change is harmless and potentially even speeds up appendTo, etc. slightly.</p>\n</div>\";}'),(33,'2nd March','a:4:{i:0;s:308:\"<div class=\"git fullItem\">\n	<div class=\"commitTime\">This is everyting22:03</div>\n	<p><strong>jQuery</strong>Added in Ben Alman\'s proposed event.namespace property (the property holds the namespaces specified in a call to trigger). Additionally fixes namespaces with .live(). Fixes #6208 and #6209.</p>\n</div>\";i:1;s:193:\"<div class=\"git fullItem\">\n	<div class=\"commitTime\">This is everyting18:03</div>\n	<p><strong>jQuery</strong>Make sure that we don\'t try to remove data from an applet. Re-Fixes #1675.</p>\n</div>\";i:2;s:179:\"<div class=\"git fullItem\">\n	<div class=\"commitTime\">This is everyting15:03</div>\n	<p><strong>jQuery</strong>Add in the new level information to the closest(Array) test.</p>\n</div>\";i:3;s:253:\"<div class=\"git fullItem\">\n	<div class=\"commitTime\">This is everyting15:03</div>\n	<p><strong>jQuery</strong>We no longer support globally-triggered events on plain objects. This is a trade-off to having good garbage collection on the objects.</p>\n</div>\";}','a:4:{i:0;s:287:\"<div class=\"git item\">\n	<div class=\"commitTime\">22:03</